query.description:
Filter campaigns where ai_admazing_goal contains the specified JSON subset.

• Format: Valid JSON object (URL-encode special characters)

► Examples:
  Find campaigns optimizing for VCR:
    → ?ai_admazing_goal__contains={"type":"vcr"}

  Find campaigns with VCR target >= 85%:
    → ?ai_admazing_goal__contains={"type":"vcr","target":{"value":85,"operator":">="}}

  Find campaigns with VCR target >= 90%:
    → ?ai_admazing_goal__contains={"target":{"value":90,"unit":"percent"}}

Filter campaigns where ai_kpi_goal contains the specified JSON subset.

• Format: Valid JSON object (URL-encode special characters)
• IMPORTANT: ai_kpi_goal can be an OBJECT or an ARRAY. Use __contains for both!
• For arrays, this checks if ANY element matches the subset.

► Examples (works for both object and array formats):
  Find campaigns with VCR as KPI:
    → ?ai_kpi_goal__contains={"type":"vcr"}

  Find campaigns with viewability KPI:
    → ?ai_kpi_goal__contains={"type":"viewability"}

  Find campaigns with VCR target >= 85%:
    → ?ai_kpi_goal__contains={"type":"vcr","target":{"value":85,"operator":">="}}

  Find campaigns with target value 90%:
    → ?ai_kpi_goal__contains={"target":{"value":90,"unit":"percent"}}

► Array example - if ai_kpi_goal is [{type:"vcr",...}, {type:"viewability",...}]:
  This query matches because array CONTAINS an element with type=vcr:
    → ?ai_kpi_goal__contains={"type":"vcr"}

Filter campaigns where ai_secondary_kpi_goal contains the specified JSON subset.

• Format: Valid JSON object (URL-encode special characters)

► Examples:
  Find campaigns with VCR as secondary KPI:
    → ?ai_secondary_kpi_goal__contains={"type":"vcr"}

  Find campaigns with traffic as secondary KPI:
    → ?ai_secondary_kpi_goal__contains={"type":"traffic"}

  Find campaigns with engagement_rate as secondary KPI:
    → ?ai_secondary_kpi_goal__contains={"type":"engagement_rate"}

  Find campaigns with VCR target >= 85%:
    → ?ai_secondary_kpi_goal__contains={"type":"vcr","target":{"value":85,"operator":">="}}

Filter campaigns where ai_target_audience contains the specified JSON subset.

• Format: Valid JSON object (URL-encode special characters)
• For array fields (countries, interests, cities), include the array in the query.
• Query matches if the array CONTAINS the specified elements.

► Examples - Scalar values:
  Find campaigns targeting females:
    → ?ai_target_audience__contains={"gender":{"value":"female"}}

  Find campaigns with min_age 18:
    → ?ai_target_audience__contains={"min_age":{"value":18}}

  Find P25-35 demographic (age 25-35):
    → ?ai_target_audience__contains={"min_age":{"value":25},"max_age":{"value":35}}

► Examples - Array fields (countries, interests, cities):
  Find campaigns targeting Argentina:
    → ?ai_target_audience__contains={"countries":{"value":["Argentina"]}}

  Find campaigns targeting United States:
    → ?ai_target_audience__contains={"countries":{"value":["United States"]}}

  Find campaigns targeting BOTH US and Argentina (must have both):
    → ?ai_target_audience__contains={"countries":{"value":["United States","Argentina"]}}

  Find campaigns with gaming interest:
    → ?ai_target_audience__contains={"interests":{"value":["gaming"]}}

